Where were the 'open door notes'? September 29, 2009 12:00 am By , NEW YORK, September 29 – Former Federal Reserve chairman Alan Greenspan on Monday denied allegations by US lawmakers that he misled them about the health of the banking system in the run-up to the 2008 financial crisis. Testifying before a congressional panel, Greenspan said there were "no secret instructions" to bank executives that they should not reveal financial problems. "I never said one thing to Wall Street banks privately and another thing to the American public," Greenspan told the Senate Banking Committee.

What is the basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue? Describe the process of muscle contraction. The contraction of skeletal muscles (muscle contraction) is initiated by a nerve impulse that travels along the axon of a motor neuron and causes the sarcoplasmic reticulum to release calcium ions. The calcium ions bind to troponin, which changes shape, allowing myosin heads to bind to the actin filaments. The myosin heads pull the actin filaments toward the center of the sarcomere, causing the sarcomere to shorten. The sarcomere shortens until the myosin heads detach from the actin filaments. The sarcomere then relaxes to its original length
